gkwreg 1.1.0
  • Reference

    Summary Method for Generalized Kumaraswamy Regression Models

    summary.gkwreg.Rd

    Computes and returns a detailed statistical summary of a fitted Generalized Kumaraswamy (GKw) regression model. The summary provides extensive information about parameter estimates, their standard errors, confidence intervals, and model fit statistics.

    # S3 method for class 'gkwreg'
summary(object, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

    Arguments

    object

    An object of class "gkwreg", typically the result of a call to gkwreg.

    conf.level

    Confidence level for the confidence intervals. Default is 0.95.

    ...

    Additional arguments (not used).

    Value

    An object of class "summary.gkwreg" with the following components:

    call

    The original function call that created the model.

    family

    Distribution family used in the model.

    coefficients

    Table of coefficient estimates, standard errors, z-values, and p-values.

    conf.int

    Matrix of confidence intervals for the coefficients.

    link

    List of link functions used for each parameter.

    fitted_parameters

    List of fitted parameter means.

    residuals

    Summary statistics of the model residuals.

    nobs

    Number of observations used in the model.

    npar

    Number of parameters in the model.

    df.residual

    Residual degrees of freedom.

    loglik

    Log-likelihood of the fitted model.

    aic

    Akaike Information Criterion.

    bic

    Bayesian Information Criterion.

    rmse

    Root Mean Square Error.

    efron_r2

    Efron's pseudo-R-squared.

    mean_absolute_error

    Mean absolute error, if available.

    convergence

    Convergence status.

    iterations

    Number of iterations performed by the optimizer.

    Details

    This method creates a comprehensive summary of the fitted GKw regression model. It provides:

    • Model call and family information

    • A detailed coefficient table with estimates, standard errors, z-values, p-values, and confidence intervals

    • Link functions for each parameter

    • Fitted parameter means and their distributions

    • Extensive model fit statistics

    • Residual analysis summary

    • Convergence information

    For the coefficient table, significant p-values are marked with stars based on common significance levels (0.001, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1).

    See also

    gkwreg

    Examples

    if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# Fit a Kumaraswamy regression model
kw_reg <- gkwreg(y ~ x1 + x2 | x1 + x2, data = df, family = "kw")

# Generate detailed summary
summary_kw <- summary(kw_reg)

# Print summary
print(summary_kw)

# Extract coefficient table
coef(summary_kw)
} # }
